instances  this  class  are  selectable  user  interface  objects  that  represent  range  positive  numeric  values  any  given  moment  given  slider  will  have  single  selection  that  considered  its  value  which  constrained  within  the  range  values  the  slider  represents  that  between  its  minimum  and  maximum  values  typically  sliders  will  made  five  areas  arrow  button  for  decrementing  the  value  page  decrement  area  for  decrementing  the  value  larger  amount  thumb  for  modifying  the  value  mouse  dragging  page  increment  area  for  incrementing  the  value  larger  amount  arrow  button  for  incrementing  the  value  based  their  style  sliders  are  either  code  horizontal  code  which  have  left  facing  button  for  decrementing  the  value  and  right  facing  button  for  incrementing  code  vertical  code  which  have  upward  facing  button  for  decrementing  the  value  and  downward  facing  buttons  for  incrementing  some  platforms  the  size  the  slider  thumb  can  varied  relative  the  magnitude  the  range  values  represents  that  relative  the  difference  between  its  maximum  and  minimum  values  typically  this  used  indicate  some  proportional  value  such  the  ratio  the  visible  area  document  the  total  amount  space  that  would  take  display  swt  supports  setting  the  thumb  size  even  the  underlying  platform  does  not  but  this  case  the  appearance  the  slider  will  not  change  styles  horizontal  vertical  events  selection  note  only  one  the  styles  horizontal  and  vertical  may  specified  important  this  class  not  intended  subclassed  see scroll bar
